Text: The experience I had involved me being approached by a seemingly sweet girl from my congregation. She mentioned that she had hated me for most of her life, because my sisters and I were the ideal family and had the ideal relationship – that her parents wanted to see in her and in her sister. I remember turning red, maybe a bit white too, and having no idea how to respond to the statement. I, a rabbis daughter, and from a family of seven have always felt like I was being watched – as if I was in a social fishbowl. However, I never realized that I was being resented at the same time. I remember walking away from the experience, half in shock + half in tears.

in this picture I am in AP History and the lights are off so that everyone can see my Powerpoint presentation. It is a small class, and I think the other students resented the fact that for my presentation I brought a laptop with movies. I knew this and felt uncomfortable about it. As I am speaking to the class, basically reading the presentation I feel like I am stuttering my words and that I look stupid to them. At the end of the presentation everyone claps but it doesn’t seem to me like it went over as well as I wanted it to. My expectations were probably too high and I felt like nobody liked it because it was with a laptop.

I walk back from the bathroom where I just changed into my shorts and t-shirt. I get to the door of the referee’s room at the hockey rink where I put my equipment on an the coaches put their skates on before practice. The door locks automatically, so I knocked the head coach flings the door open and sits back down. In front of me I see the assistant coach, whom I have a crush on, standing there in his underwear. Startled, he jumps behind the wall separating the shower from the rest of the room. I just walk in, sit down, and start to get dressed.

There were flashing lights, strobe lights to be exact. Many people are dancing to the loud music. At times, smoke would stream out from the smoke machines. Alcoholic drinks are on the table; some people are drinking them and smoking cigarettes. A lot of girls are dancing very closely with guys. A few girls are dancing amongst themselves, no guys with them. One of them later on drinks a lot until she’s sick,

I see lots of people in the high school gym getting their yearbooks and having friends sign them. I remember seeing some friends around, but it seemed like I didn’t have enough, and I ended up asking people I didn’t know very well to sign my book.

I am standing in line for pizza in the high school cafeteria. I love pepperoni pizza, so that’s what I plan on getting. 2 girls are standing behind me that are seniors, and popular seniors at that. I overhear one of them saying that they wanted pepperoni too. When I get to the front of the line, I notice there is only one piece of pepperoni left. I wanted these girls to like me so I order cheese instead, so the girl behind me can have the last pepperoni. I turn around to tell them this (make it clear what I’ve done for her), but they don’t understand what I am talking about because I am not making any sense. I feel so stupid! & just walk off, embarrassed

A GIRL IS LISTENING TO THIS KID’S CD PLAYER… SHE DROPS IT ON THE GROUND, COMPLETELY BREAKING IT IN HALF. ANGERED, HE GRABS HOLD OF HER SHOULDERS AND SHAKES HER IN A MOCK-CHOKING WAY. LATER THIS GIRL TELLS HER OLDER BROTHER’S FRIEND AN EXAGGERATED ACCOUNT OF THE STORY. HE FINDS THE KID, THROWS HIM UP AGAINST A LOCKER AND THREATENS TO BEAT HIM. FOR THE NEXT FEW DAYS, THE KID WHOSE CD PLAYER WAS BROKEN IS AFRAID TO COME TO SCHOOL. DESPITE APOLOGIZING TO THE GIRL, AND HER BROTHER, THE KID IS STILL HARASSED FOR WEEKS.

it is dark but lit in Miami 2 kids are on a street corner next to a liquor store. They are going around asking people who might not care to buy them alcohol. Some people tell them no but one bum asks them for $5 to go in and buy a few 40’s and pick up their alcohol. When the bum came out the 2 kids followed him trying to be inconspicuous to an alley.

At a party my senior year of high school, I remember feeling very awkward + out of place. Never a part of the “party/cool” crowd, my friends + I decided to go to this party as it was a big celebration for the senior class. Walking in the door, so many people turned + looked - + the amount of people who said, “ Oh my god look who’s here” was definitely an awkward… if not truly embarrassing… moment. I spent the rest of the party just milling around + talking with friends, but the comments as I came in the door left me feeling awkward + out of place for the rest of the party.

He walked into the classroom, dressed as a typical teenager but with his hat pulled down far over his eyes. He looked around the room, as if wondering what to do. Seeing the teacher, he approached him and handed him a slip of paper. The teacher read the note, signed it and returned it to the student. The student stood there paralyzed, until the teacher directed him to a seat. He said nothing, and made no eye contact with other students.

I am in a car with Dan, an old friend of mine that I had grown apart from, driving and his little brother Max sitting near me, as well as his friend Rich, who was an angry guy from a broken household. Dan and Rich are smoking, and the windows are partly down, My head’s near one of them so I can breathe; Max isn’t so lucky. The music’s loud enough to make my ears hurt, but I don’t have the assertiveness to ask to lower the volume. I don’t remember many seatbelts being worn. The car seems crowded, and Dan and Rich are dressed a bit punkishly. The car is a grayish boxy eighties car, like a Chevy or Pontiac.

I am in physics class during one of the times that we are free to work on the assigned homework problems in groups. My best friend and I know the teacher, Mr. Clark, pretty well. We come in before school, during homeroom, and lunch often to get help with the homework and the labs that we mess up. So we were joking with him. Courtney, another girl in the class, makes some remark. I feel uncomfortable. She makes fun of us for being in physics so much and wants to know why we care so much or why we are there. I know that I don’t like the class anymore than she does, but don’t want to admit to having fun. My best friend and I probably received unfair treatment since we got to do extra credit projects, which I also didn’t want to admit to.

The US History classroom is sunny, it is late in the schoolyear – spring. Brett + I are standing by our seats. We are the first to arrive because we have Spanish together right across the hall the period before. (In Spanish, the assignment for that day was to bring in an object and tell about it + describe it to the class in Spanish. I brought in a jar of fetal cats from a vet’s office and Brett brought a Pirhanna embedded in a piece of glass.) We are both holding our dead animal *show + tell* props from Spanish class. Brett comments that we both brought dead animals for Spanish + I agree. (I think Brett seems like a cool person – I have a couple of other classes w/ him – and kind of have a crush on him, so I want to say something to continue the conversation. But I can’t think of anything so the exchange ends + the rest of class finds its way in.

A FEW OF MY FRIENDS & I WERE COMPLETELY INFATUATED W/ OUR 22 YR. OLD CHEMISTRY TEACHER, SOPHOMORE YEAR. WE WERE STANDING IN LINE TO GET LUNCH & WE WERE TALKING VERY “FAVORABLY” ABOUT HIM WHEN WE REALIZED THAT HE WAS STANDING RIGHT BEHIND US IN LINE. OF COURSE, I WAS THE LOUDEST & THE MOST “GRAPHIC” W/ MY STATEMENTS – SO IT WAS EXTREMELY HUMILIATING. I TURNED RED, FELT AS THOUGH I WAS GOING TO CRY & TRIED TO IGNORE HIS PRESENCE AS HE STOOD BEHIND US, GRINNING.

It is the band’s Christmas party and all the bandmembers are sitting around talking, eating, and some dancing. I am seated with two other people, my best friend and his girlfriend. I am looking a bit confused and awkward because the two of them clearly look like they want to be alone, but there are no seats left for me to go to. They are basically huddled together at one end of the small ta*** and I am on the other end, sort of at the edge of my seat. My eyes keep **hunting** around for a chance to get out of the situation, but I just keep sitting there, saying nothing.

It was my first day at a new high school. The bell rang for lunch and I asked someone where the cafeteria was.  Then I got my lunch from home and went to find the cafeteria. Before I walked in I could see inside through the 2 small windows on the double doors that led to the cafeteria. The room seemed small to me, but the crowd seemed huge. I walked in and there was a lot of activity going on inside and it was very loud. I looked around searching for any familiar face, but I couldn’t find one. Then I searched for tables with empty chairs. I asked people at 3 different tables if I could sit with them, but they said the chairs were saved. So, I had to leave the cafeteria and eat outside alone.

I remember going to one cheesy h.s. dance It was uncomfortable because no matter how many people were there the room always felt empty. I got there earlier than my friends so I was by myself. It was uncomfortable because I knew people their but no one well enough to hang around. I just kept scurrying from place to place trying to look like I was preoccupied. I was to shy and nerve-wracked to actually try and interact w/ others. I hung around the phone pretending I had to make a phone call. It was a long line. When I got on the phone I called people who I knew wouldn’t be home.

This happened after a graded math test paper had been given back to the students (me and my classmates). The test was usually pretty difficult, so the mean is quite low. However, a few of my classmates and I always did well on these tests. But the awkward thing is that I usually didn’t want others to know my grade. This is not because I was modest or whatsoever. This is just because I figured out sometimes when I let my classmates whose grades were low know my high grade, they would think I was kind of different from them. In short, they would envy me. In order to avoid isolation, I usually mentioned my grade as ok and didn’t let them to see my paper though they might have guessed that I did get an actually good grade.

I was at a track meet with some other teammates just talking between events. I was a senior and there was a sophomore who apparently had a crush on me. He repeatedly asked me while we were sitting there to ask him to the Sadie Hawkins dance. I didn’t want to, so I said no. Anyway, I was sitting on a railing, he was sitting next to me, and a friend of mine was sitting next to me on the other side. We were looking out at the track. He was smiling and joking but I could tell he was also serious. When I picture it, there aren’t other people really close by, but there are a lot of people in the building, The other people are just a blur. I can see all of our track stuff below us, the shape of the building, and the way I was sitting on the railing.

The girl is wearing a black sweater and purple skirt and black loafers. She leans over the shoulder of a boy with blond hair, wearing a green sweater. She looks nervous and her cheeks are pink with embarrassment. There are crutches on the floor next to the folding metal chair where he is sitting; it’s also a cafeteria, and the lights are off. The boy is shaking his head; his forehead is wrinkled. No one is left in the cafeteria and the hallway outside is noisy with students returning home.

I was standing at my locker getting ready to leave school when one of my guy friends walked up to me. He handed me a flower and asked me if I wanted to go out with him. I stood there, not saying anything for a long time. I wasn’t sure if he meant on a date or just as friends, so I asked him. He didn’t know how to respond. Finally I realized he meant on a date. I dint like him so I didn’t know how to respond. I said I’d let him know later. He turned bright red, said “ok” and walked away.

He met his English teacher on the stairs of the teacher’s common room, he looked awkward and guilty of something, and then started to apologize profusely. The teacher looks ******ed and after saying something to him, walks away. He then drops his shoulders and walks away, looking somewhat depressed.

There were 4 or 5 of my friends studying in one of my friend’s basement. Previously I had told some of them an embarrassing detail about my friend Adam hoping he would never find out. Unfortunately Sam chose this moment to start making fun of Adam for it. Adam fanatically denied it and promptly left the room to sulk. But not before he gave me a horrendously dirty look.

In the image, both myself and my student (a non-native English speaker) are sitting at a table in the library, across from each other. I seem to be having trouble communicating with my, both from my facial expression and my heavy use of body language. At the other end of the table, my student seems to be just as clueless and distracted.

I see myself talking in fragments that are hard to understand but I can see what I was saying. I was sitting @ a desk during a club meeting and one of the officer asked me a question about the UCLA Course Booklet I had and how I got it. The officer asked a simple Question and I answered. As an outsider, all it sounded like was fragments and a little bit of accent.

I’m standing in a high school cafeteria during my boyfriend’s semi-formal. He’s introducing me to a whole group of friends whom I haven’t met before. I’m trying to be friendly but I feel very intimidated by all of them. I feel like I am being scrutinized by all of them to determine whether I’m a good enough for my boyfriend. I feel very awkward because I’m not sure how to act or what to say. I want them to like me, but I don’t have the confidence to be outgoing and relaxed about it.

This is difficult to do because in a way, I was the observer. (I may have slightly misunderstood the question…) But from another’s visual perspective it would have looked like this: 9 or 10 people sleeping on floor/couches in living room after prom. Girl on one couch, her boyfriend on the floor. The boyfriend, thinking everyone else is asleep, tries to make an advance on another girl. There is another person awake though, (me) and the boyfriend finds this out and asks the awake person to not tell the girlfriend. This makes the awake person feel very awkward because both the girlfriend & boyfriend are her friends and she doesn’t want to have to take sides but feels the girlfriend should know about what happened. Relationships then, became strained between all three friends.

We drove to McDonald’s down on 13 and had lunch, then decided we should take a sign once held up by suction cups (McDonald’s ad), I ended up sticking it on my front door until my Dad caught on and threw it away.

Two of my girlfriends and I climbed up on the roof of our high school one night. We walked around, exploring a bit, taking in the view, walking on beams, yelling a bit sometimes, just being silly and adventurous.

It was pom competition and we were performing. We’re all smiling because we have to, wearing blue tight uniforms with silver poms, have our hair in curled pony tails, and we are wearing lots of makeup. The audience in our section is standing and cheering it’s in the Blair H.S Gym.

It was the night after we got our rings (and became old girls). There was a tradition where once you become an old girl you can wear all black. So my friends and I (we were only 14) dressed up all in black and pretended we were Oprishniki (the bearers of all traditions – otherwise known as the scariest people on campus). We looked ridiculous we pantyhose in our hair, black clothes, and black makeup. We actually fooled quite a few people before we were caught.
laying on the beach at night watching the sky and talking with my friends
My friends and I were at pleasure island in Florida. We were posing for pictures underneath a railing, with the camera person above us. We were tan, happy, and excited to be cut.

We (a bunch of wild cross country runners) are gliding up to the water tower in the dark, on IC’s campus, with bottles of spray paint in the bag, laughing loudly (but muffled) and keeping an eye out for cops. Once up there, we go crazy and cover the tower with our art = our memories.

We held a surprise birthday party for one of our friends at a friend’s house. Before one of our friends went to pick the birthday girl up, we hid and turned off the lights.  When she came, we all jumped out. She seemed very happy. Some of our friends went home after the celebration, but some of us, including me, slept over.

My girlfriend, best friend, and his girlfriend and I went to a local supermarket and had a water fight in the aisle of the store. Then my friend and I bought flip-flops, aviator sunglasses, and tee shirts that were made for 50 year olds and had sayings about being 50 years old on them. We put all these on and walked around the store.
We were at Dave & Buster’s having a fun time after prom and I was playing all of the ticket games to try to get some prices to take home with me. My friends were playing other games

I went to a local theme park with some close friends and we went on a “kiddy” coaster (a roller coaster for children) and the ride was so slow and not amusing at all.  The conductor voluntarily gave us free consecutive rides – which we didn’t want. I just remember looking back at my friends and laughing at our misfortune.

We are sitting at Willie C’s Café following a performance of “Celebrate the Century”, my senior year dance performance.  Next to me are two of my closest friends and we are all alternating between laughing because we’re having so much fun and crying because we know that we’ll all be leaving soon for different schools.

My boyfriend told me that we were going to see a movie with my best friend Jules and her prom date, Todd. I had planned this out with Jules for weeks! When we got to Jule’s house to pick them up I walked in the door and all of my best friends and people I love including my family jumped out and yelled suprise! Everyone was smiling and yelling happy birthday and I was so suprised and happy.

After we lost in the first round my senior friends and I sat in the dugout with our heads hung low and our brims over our eyes. No one said anything because there was nothing to say. We would never win a championship.
Sitting in my friends kitchen on a stool w/ two of our other friends dying easter eggs
After lacrosse practice, we all went into the pool area and decided to go swimming in the pool. We are laughing and smiling and just talking about the day.

We were on a classtrip in catskills mts. We had just come back from skiing and we were watching TV in our rooms. They were showing “The Storm of the Century”, a Steven King movie, and after a couple of minutes we unanimously decided to turn the TV off (it was too scary); we then turned off the light and got into bed. A minute or so later the phone rang and I (still scared from the movie) screamed; and everyone else jumped out of bed and scream to. I was in the middle of the room when the light were turned on and we heard some tapping on the window, we screamed again and we all stumbled out of the room. A classmate was locked out so she was trying to get someone to let her in hence the phone & window.

We are trying to make a rubber band-powered car. Angie and I are crouching over the car on the hardwood floor in her kitchen, try to bend the propeller so it moves the car. We are getting a little hopeless, but laughing because it seems impossible. Janet is in the kitchen cooking something in a pot for us to eat.

It’s spring time, volleyball season, practice is cancelled. Some of the seniors, ***** members of the team, decide to go to the beach to play v-ball there. They set up a net and play joyfully along the ocean until the sun sets.  For that brief period, time froze. Nothing else mattered to them. No one had any problems at this time. Everyone was just having the time of their life w/ the people who mattered most to them. One can see it on the peaceful expressions on their faces.

My friends + I went out last Friday to bars. We were all giddy before going out and decided to all wear sunglasses (on spring break there was a group of people who always did this + we thought it was funny). We spent the night out together and had a great time. We didn’t really talk to anyone else.

We all sat around a large circular table, lavished with colorful food, drinks and flowers. Cameras held in one hand, forks in the other we chatted for hours. We were all well dressed, I had flowers in my ornately done hair, and I wore a pale yellow dress. My date sat to my left, my best friend to my right.

At a party a few weeks before high school graduation at a teacher’s house. There was lots of good food and music. There was lots of alcohol & everyone was very drunk. We all had such a good time together: laughing, playing volleyball, swimming. Everyone was very happy to be there. Everyone was so relieved.
I was in London with five of my friends at someone’s house for lunch. We were all sitting at a table eating & talking. I was wearing a white skirt & a blue shirt.

I bought beer with a fake ID, went back to my car, and put the beer in the trunk. Then to get back to the party, I made an illegal U-turn and got pulled over by a cop. I was scared he saw me walk out of the store + would see my age on my real ID.

One night a few weeks before graduation about 5 of us sneaked out of our dorms (boarding school) and just spent the whole night lying in the grass and talking. I remember it well because it was probably the only time I ever broke the rules. We talked about anything and everything, and it was just a great experience (especially since we didn’t get caught.)
I was at a football game and I was watching my friend run around the bleachers, all dressed up, trying to win a contest for the most crazy fan.

I am riding in the limo with 4 other couples. Jason keeps playing with the radio. All the girls are fixing their dresses and hair. The seats are black leather and there is a big bump on the left side of the floor. Rini keeps putting her feet on it. I am wearing blue.

We were walking in the mall. My friend Michelle was wearing a baby blue sweater and Kahla was with us by the movie theatres in the mall. There was an arcade to our right as we were walking and Michelle was drinking an orange juice as she walked into a pole that me and Kahla went around. I hunched over laughing as did Kahla. This young boy also saw and smiled.

I was at a party at my friend’s house. I was standing in the kitchen with Jenny, Julie, Shannon, Heidi, and Julia. Meat ******* came on the radio and Jenny started singing along really loudly.  We all joined in. We were between the fridge + the microwave.

My two friends and I are standing at the front of an empty church. It is early afternoon so the light pouring through the stained glass windows are still strong but fading. We are a church band rehearsing a song for recording. Each of us is intently focused on our instruments and not watching each other. The music is horrible.

Going home from NYC on the bus after a whole Saturday having fun + sightseeing. It was 100° and Yael was asleep on my shoulder… James + Anju + I were watching the lit city as we left. We were so high up on the bridge it was like flying, + though I was tired it had been a great day.
I went to NYC with my best friend to celebrate our graduation. We went to a nice restaurant for dinner, and then we went back to our hotel rooms and changed to go to the clubs.

I’m at one of my friend’s houses. There is a group of about 10 of us watching a video. It is a photo montage two of my friends put together of our time in high school. We are sitting on the floor + couches in my friend’s basement. We’re laughing + reminiscing about the pictures on the TV. It’s a bittersweet moment as we prepare for graduation.

This past summer, I was standing in a long winding line at an amusement park with eight or so of my friends. It was sunny and mildly warm. After finally getting on the big, old rickety rollercoaster and riding it, I was so energized and happy – as were all of my friends.

John Vorassi’s graduation party – I am very friendly and approachable, smoking, drinking, moving from person to person. I’m wearing a green hooded shirt with orange under. I seem very comfortable w/ who I am. It is night, outside.

My last day back home, before college, my friends + I took one last round about the town. I was the only one going away for college, so it was damn special for me. We didn’t do very much, just drove around and talked and drank, went to a bar, and then roamed the streets of Vancouver. There was a lot of laughter as friends stumbled around.
Sitting on the bench on Fire island. I was sitting reading a book w/ my ex-girlfriend. My two best friends and their girlfriends were in the water.

I am picturing a party that my friends and I threw senior year of high school for new years. I see myself standing around laughing with some friends. I see the random people (not my close friends) who showed up that night and who I have not seen since high school.

Tina wore a traditional Thai clothes today and some un traditional Thai Dance. We sat on grassland corner of the park and circled her. She stood in the center of the circle. She looks so happy today and told us that she just learned how to dance Thai dance.

I remember the walk to the club – what everyone was wearing (also helps that I still look at pictures from it) – pairing up to make getting in easier… and then my friend Samantha and I going off on our own as soon as we got in ( to be more ‘mature’, not in a group). And then I remember the whole night at the club - what music was playing, the people we talked to there, etc.
I, and some classmates of mine, did not do so well on the AP Bio exam. I in particular had purposely failed it. The school was angry with us and we were being lectured/ punished for failing the test.

Two girls sneak out of their H.S. during 5th period. They run past security get in one of the girls car and try to leave undetected. They both try to keep their heads below the dashboard so no one can see them.

We were joking around, my friends and I as it was the day classes ended for good (highschool anyway) and we were all joyful as we went on a mission to hunt down the girl I liked. It was the most ridiculous us jumping around as we headed for Elmur****.
We went to Six Flags for our senior trip + went on the “Rip Cord” ride in which you plummet toward the ground 250 feet. You end up swinging like a pendulum until the operator stops you.
In my H.S. physics classroom with my friend. We got into an argument. It’s a sunny day. We’re sitting in our seats.
Sunlight reflected off the lake. Peachy, Shelley, and **** had looks of disbelief on their faces as I snuck up behind the goose with a ferocious yell. I chased the goose into the water.

IT WAS MY BIRTHDAY. WE WERE SITTING NEXT TO THE POOL ON A SMALL WITH SOME EXTRA CHAIRS PULLED UP. THERE WERE SIX PEOPLE WITH ME AND THEY HAD JUST GIVEN ME MY GIFT ($350 VOUCHER AT A MUSIC STORE). IT WAS SUNNY AND I COULDN’T THANK THEM ENOUGH. WE WERE ALL LAUGHING AND TALKING THERE ABOUT THE PAST.

We are on my tennis court and there are a couple of tents set up and we are playing cards, Mike is mixing drinks, our cars line the driveway. Krista, Gauick and Joe are also there with sleeping bags and we are acting wild, but trying to remain quiet.

me and my friends are paint-balling on a school trip, its been quiet for the last couple of minutes so at the fork on the road in the woods i shot on of my friend in the back out of boredom, then he shot me, while we were distracted the other team took us out of the game.

It was the senior night football game and it was cold and raining and we were all standing on the field with out parents as the announcer was announcing our names and bios. It was also the Halloween themed game so the student section was dressed in Halloween costumes. We all had to wear sweatpants and jackets and gloves since it was so cold and everyone was excited since it was senior night.

We were in my friend Alec's basement. Sam and Wayne were there as well. It was in the midst of competition season, but we happened to have a weekend off. To the left were some tables with leftover frozen pizzas on them. We had three TV's set up, each with our own systems, Alec having the biggest TV in the middle of the room. Alec, Wayne and I had our PS4's while Sam didn't. We were taking turns with the controller as we played games all night. Later on, I remember we were watching stand up comedy on Netflix (I think Kevin Hart?) and laughing uncontrollably. I fell asleep on the couch around midnight and woke up to Alec and Wayne still awake. Sam crashed on the floor with a piece of pizza in his hand.

The whole day, I was with my friends and our families. Everyone was happy for the same reason. At the actual event, all of my senior class and some others were all treating the night with a sort of finality. There are some people that I haven't seen since prom, and I'm unsure as to when I might see them again. As a whole, the night was enjoyable, and I got to spend more time with my closest friends afterwards. I remember how everyone looked, and the people whom I remember most from the event are the people I consider my closest friends. Not everyone stayed the entire time, and I don't know what they thought was preferable. Everyone was sitting with their respective groups to begin with, and some people just went to a different place with their same groups.

I am standing behind a booth at the country club where my prom was held. Across from me is my best friend Alisa and next her is our friend Faizah and her sister Marihah. In the chairs across from the booth are three more of our friends. Some of the are fidgeting with the plastic light up ice cubes that are in the cups on the table; others are taking videos for their snap chat. Alisa and I are discussing where we are going to go after prom.
I am on a roller coaster at cedar point and it is going really fast and the wind is blowing in my face.
I can see the football team clearly since I am in the front row of the student section. My friends are on either side of me. I look up to dark clouds and see how it might rain soon.

There are a lot of toys around me and I am sitting with a homeless kid in the women's shelter. I find out he is a little slow with his actions and even though he is four years old, he still can not walk or talk. I felt really bad for him and I try to help him out.

It is the evening of my senior prom. I arrive at the park to take pictures with my friends, and once that is done we go out to dinner at a nice restaurant. I carpool with my friends and we arrive at the prom. It is cold outside but warm inside. It is decorated nicely inside and vibrant lights are flashing, while music I don't listen to is blaring loud. Most of the night is spent socializing with the other seniors from my school, knowing that soon we all will graduate and not see each other again.

I tried my best to walk gracefully in high-heels and stand up straight. I couldn't stop smiling and laughing while I danced with my date. The food I ate was delicious and the salad dressing was bomb. I sat at a table with people who didn't like me. I still had plenty of fun. I found myself not wanting the night to ends and I loved the compliments people gave me on my dress. I liked walking everywhere with confidence and the good looks I got from people. It made me feel good about myself.
I am in the art room.

I am sitting in the third booth in the Noodles and company. My best friend, Emily, is sitting across from me. Johnny had walked in with Ben and noticed us and is sitting on a stool near our table and we are all looking at each other questioningly.

We are walking along a path in the pitch black. As we approach the cabin we hear these gunshots coming from the house. But before we can worry our friends dad pops out and starts lighting another firework.

I am in the Robert Morris University in Chicago esports arena. Me and my closest friends all sit at a long table with computers in front of all 5 of us. I see my friends with their headsets on as they communicate what we will do in order to win this league of legends game and secure third place at state. We just came off of a loss, so the pressure is on to secure the victory. Every single one of my friends is determined, filled with the a blazing passion to play our hearts out doing something we love. There is a moment of pause during picks and bans, and my friend accidentally bans the character I intended to play, so I play a more unconventional character that the other team doesn't see coming. We started the build in my friend's living room. We gathered all the boxes he ordered off of amazon and put a comedy special off of Netflix in the background. I remember that it was a particularly enjoyable one, but I cannot recall the name. We started by unboxing the motherboard and sorting out the stuff inside. Then we unboxed the processor, which was an easy and fast install the motherboard. We continued with the RAM and storage, then unboxed the biggest box, the case. We set the case it's on its side on a table and installed the motherboard, screwing in all the necessary screws. Once that was done, we opened the back panel of the case and started te longest part of the build, organizing the cables. This step by itself probably took an hour, and once that was done and we were satisfied, we installed the graphics card. This was the last part of the build and once we were done, we moved the computer up to my friend's room. He had already set up his new monitor and keyboard so we just had to plug in all the USB and display cables into their corresponding ports. Once that was all and finish, I lent him a USB drive with the windows installer. We installed Windows and the computer was then officially completed. All that was left to do was for him to install all his programs and games, which took a bit of time since the internet connection was not that fast. As the programs were installing, we decided to pass the time by playing Super Smash Bros Ultimate on his switch. We invited another friend over and played for hours into the night. We actually pulled an all-nighter playing since we were so hyped up on soda and energy drinks that the next morning we decided to go to Starbucks and The Official Pancake House. I ordered a large veggie omelet while he ordered strawberry pancakes. After breakfast, we were exhausted and he drove us home so we could finally sleep.

It was the day after the state semi final game after losing 1-0 and being kicked out of the tournament, just one game away from the state finals game that would be held in Columbus. Our whole team gathered in our coaches classroom confused on everything that was happening. It was said that, the team we lost to, played with an extra player for approximately 8 minutes in the second half of the game. The film was being watched, everyone was sitting in the room, shocked, livid, and upset. The principle brought the whole team down to the office and the whole word was out around the school that the other team cheated. After returning from the office, students all around would come up to us asking if anything important happened. once again, the whole team got called to the office and was told the news was outside, speak to no one. The whole crazy day everyone wanted to know what the whole outcome would be and if the other team would get in trouble for their actions. No one knew if they would be disqualified from the tournament, and we would actually end up in the state finals. Also, we weren't aware if the state would even do anything about this. The whole day was the whole team just anxious and waiting for an answer that never came.

Visual imagery plays a prominent role in mental simulations of past and future events: people tend to “see” events in their mind's eye when they think about them. When picturing events people often use their own first-person perspective, looking out at the situation through their own eyes. However, other times people use a third-person perspective, so that they see themselves in the image from the visual perspective an observer would have. This chapter presents a theoretical model proposing that imagery perspective functions to determine whether people understand events bottom-up, in terms of the phenomenology evoked by concrete features of the pictured situation (first-person), or top-down, in terms of abstractions that integrate the pictured event with its broader context (third-person). This model integrates existing findings and generates novel predictions that challenge widespread assumptions about the function that imagery perspective serves. We review a program of research that supports these predictions, demonstrating the role of imagery perspective in defining the experiential and conceptual facets of the self, determining emotional responses to recalled and imagined life events, and shaping forecasts of future behavior and emotion. We conclude by discussing how the proposed model helps to distinguish the visual dimension of perspective from other dimensions on which perspective may vary. We consider how this model connects with other theories concerning the self and event representation, and we explore the implications for classic and contemporary areas of social psychological inquiry including attribution, social perspective-taking, culture, emotional coping, and top-down versus bottom-up processing.

i am in my school and i walk up to my social studies teacher as she steps out of the class she just finished .I excuse my self and go to her and ask her if she is pregnant .To my embarrassment i find out she is not . I am in the realtor's office, with my realtor and mortgage adviser there. The seller's realtor comes in, and soon the keys to my first house are being handed to me.

I am looking at my manager sitting in his office chair and about to tell him I'm officially quitting for good. I had already "quit" when I went on maternity leave but had needed to come back to support my family after my husband got laid off. I inform my manager that I will not be coming back to work. I was officially done and to take me off the books. After 9 years of that place, I was through! I am sitting at the bar of the restaurant looking out into the dining area. While it is only mid-day, the restaurant's lights are low and it's a little hazy from the smoking area. Close to the front of the restaurant near the host stand is sitting a young women and a man, presumably her husband or boyfriend. I find her very attractive and am distracted, and keep looking over in her direction. The daylight from the street is shining in through the door of the restaurant so she and her dining companion are lit from behind. As I am leaving a little while after they sat down I walk right by their table, excuse myself as I am passing, saying something along the lines of 'I'm sorry to interrupt your lunch but just wanted to comment on how attractive you are and what a lucky man to have you as a girlfriend.' Far from a gracious compliment, it was awkward and I was immediately embarrassed, not even staying long enough to hear their response before I turned towards the front door, walked past the host stand that was just behind them, and exited to the bright street.

I am sitting in a Mexican restaurant and talking to someone I know is very important to me but we just met. I have social anxiety so I am nervous but I know this meeting is very important and that every comment I make is important. I ask her questions about her and her life and listen very intently to what she has to say.

A friend had his car battery dead on a very very col night (-30 below). I promised them I would fix it. Even though i didn't really want to, I got into my car, bought a new battery, drove to their house and fixed the battery.

Then, the nerves start to creep in, wondering and hoping that it will have been worth it, that it will, and that it will make money. i am walking down a corridor with grey hospital carpet, i am passing the cafeteria that has glass walls, i am wearing light blue jacket, with the name tag oncology pharm volunteer. i am feeling extremely nervous, because i did not thin i was going to be one of the few chosen to volunteer at this recognized cancer patient institution. as im reaching the end of the corridor, i am debating whether taking the stairs or a elevator, i am looking at my map, so i take the elevator in case, i get lost, i will find my quicker. i push the cold button number 3, to take me to floor three. i am wondering at the moment how come this elevator doesnt have music plying,in addition the metallic material is so clean, resembles a mirror, i am seeing my reflection and i look like a scared and unsure of myself, my own reflection made me feel insecure of my position for the day. as i arrive to the pharmacy, i explain to the tech i am there to volunteer and work along side the stem cell engineers., she opens the security door for me, i walk to the back of the pharmacy, without taking my eyes of the endless shelves of medications, from floor to ceiling, the air is much colder at this point, unsure if its becuae of my own nerves or because it is much colder. As i am introduced and everyone is introduced, i am aware of the room how white absolutely everything is, even the computers are white, uniforms are white, even the binders are white. i feel so out of place and dirty with the khakis i chose to wear, and the brown shirt. I am taken to a near by lab, and i am taught how different specimens are handle and cells are extracted, it is alaska cold, i cannot smell, or see anything past the placenta i am working with. handling with care, learning how to do exact cuts, prepare, and store, by the end of my 3 hour shift i have adopted a robot mind state. retrieve tissue, prepare, cut, hand to engineer, store and  repeat. As my shift ends i am so in deep thought that as im waking out the hospital ever

I have Multiple Sclerosis and I have had it for 45 years.  I now use a power wheelchair most of the time.  My son's wedding was coming up and it was so important to me to have our mother and son dance.  I was determined.  Our older son edited down a song to two minutes. We used I Wish You Love by Sam Cooke. With the help of my Physical Therapist and 5 weeks of hard work the wedding day was here and it looked like maybe this could happen. I had sparkly silver sneakers to make a fun statement to go with my beautiful gown.  We were ready.  My husband gently helped me out of my chair and my son took my hand. As the music started I concentrated on my son and staying strong as he held me.  We swayed back and forth and I was so caught up in the moment that I didn't know what was happening around us. As the music slowed to it's end, I looked up and saw guests crying, flashes going off as people took photos. It felt like paparazzi! I was crying as well. It truly was one of the best two minutes of my life.

Jennifer sat in the living room with her oud.  Learning to compose a piece for the upcoming championship for her medieval re-enactment group would be hard.  She frowned as she tuned the instrument.   Composing a piece in a historic Ottoman mode and rhythm would be especially hard after never having composed anything her whole life.  She tapped out a few rhythms on the body of her oud, thinking what would be interesting to compose in.  She tapped out the 17th century rhythm devri revan - 1-2-3 1-2-1-2 1-2-3 1-2-1-2 and thought that sounded compelling and fun to compose in.  She noodled around in a variety of musical modes with her oud, thinking of what mode sounded appealing and would be interesting and fun.  Slowly as she played form and melody took shape.  She set her oud back down in its stand, and picked up a pencil and the book of staff paper for sheet music that a friend have given her a few months later.  Alternating between playing parts of the new piece in her head and writing down phrases, in the course of a few hours the completed sheet music for the new tune had taken shape.  And she'd composed her first tune ever.  And it wasn't just any tune, but a pesrev - a complicated 4 part tune - in a historic Ottoman mode and rhythm.  She went upstairs, showed her husband the completed sheet music, then played through the whole tune on her oud for him.  Later she would enter this piece in her medieval group's competition and make it to the finals with it, but the moment that really was the accomplishment was the hard and scary work of composing the piece itself, and feeling like she could actually do it.
