It is Friday the 13th, and there are people lining around the block to get a $31 tattoo. She smiles through the pain of getting a tattoo on her ankle. She talks to her friends and asks how they're feeling.

Running the Bergandi wire weave machine at work, first meeting my friend B and him teaching me how to run the machine effectively to become a good weaver.  The machine runs wire through a wurm to form the wire into links for chain link fencing.
The event is an orientation to my job. The faculty along with other co workers are present, and are describing the environment. They detail the rules and processes of the job, and what it involves.
I went into work looking at the products I was getting ready to scan. There was no mask-wearing and people were going about their day without all of these stressful times.

I am watching a pretty funny overweight person dancing to rap music as part of some type of performance for college. Everyone around me is laughing at the display, and it seems like the person dancing is experiencing no humiliation as they dance in front of a room packed to the brim with new college students.
You see me and all my family unloading out of a SUV and start towards the Arena with no Masks headed for an Arena Football game with not a worry on our minds!

I walk into my intern position at a nearby hospital and brief with colleagues before starting my shift. Although many aspects in my life are not going to plan at the moment, I am certain things will come right. I see that everyone in my workplace is busy and focused.

We are in a large ballroom for a dance. We are pushed up against a lot of people in line for drinks at the bar. Everyone is huddled together to hear each other over the loud music. Theres maybe 200 people in the room

I am treating patients in a gym full of exercise equipment and my other fellow therapists are all there as well. I am having fun and laughing along with my co-workers, as we talk and have good conversation.

I'm running down the lane and cut across towards the goal. Kobe, maybe Cal, throws me a pass and I catch it. Immediately I get laid out and break my collar bone. I can't lift my arm, my collar bone is broken.

So the event I am thinking of doesn't revolve around the Thanksgiving holiday but, rather the month of November. I am thinking about my day-to-day life when I had a job that was largely unaffected by holidays during the month that time of year. It was a sense of normalcy I had before I was laid-off in January of 2020 after returning from the Christmas holiday with family. I remember sitting at my desk in front of my two monitors working on designing ads for local clients. One of my bosses would sit at the desk next to me where she would answer phones where she would speak to clients and customers alike. I would spend my work day correcting and designing ads in Indesign, answering emails to sales representatives and my other boss, organizing files, compiling ads into future booklets, and doing minor updates on ads for future release 1-2 months in advance. Everyday at 5pm I would clock-out, log my hours in Google Sheets, and drive home. This is what I considered normal before the Coronavirus outbreak.

I was in a decently sized crowd watching the opening act perform. I can see that people are excited for the main show, and are enjoying themselves. There are some people in front of me, between myself and the stage, but most people are behind me.

There are a couple of people (myself one of them) standing in the clothing section of a box retailer.  There are not crowds but a moderate amount of people filling the store.  The two people are shopping and chatting while they leisurely browse around the section and the store.  They are relatively slow and fairly carefree.

I was attending a seminar at my college's auditorium around 2pm on Thursday March 5th. The seminar was about sex trafficking in Texas with a panel consisting of a survivor, a judge, a police sheriff, and a lady that was a head of an organization that was working towards helping survivors of trafficking with free resources if possible. I can see myself walk into the auditorium looking for my teacher or any of my fellow classmates but the front room was crowded. Thankfully a person saw me looking around and said I should sign in on the clipboard with my name and my teachers name located on the left side of the room. I see myself walking to the table where there are a line of about 3 students signing in. Once I signed my name in, I notice that I turn to look at some stalls that are set up in the room that have information about trafficking, domestic violence, and women's safety. Since I had arrived later I did not get a chance to look at all the booths so I decided to go inside the auditorium to secure a seat before the panel started. I observe myself taking a seat in the middle section of seats near the exiting row in case my seminar went past the time it stated so I can go to my next class. The seminar started with the a woman introducing the panel and preparing us to hear from the survivor. I can only really recall some of what was said because the seminar contained a lot of information and was deeply emotional, especially when the survivor told her story. I had to leave from the lecture before it was over since I had another class to attend to. Hearing the information about how my state was a hot spot for trafficking was alarming and unsettling so I was glad I was able to attend so I was made more aware of what is happening around me.
I was sitting in a classroom with lots of other people learning about math

Three friends are at the bowling alley. They have some food at the table and two of them are eating and watching the third one bowl. The third one is in a backswing about to send the ball down the alley.

For Mother's Day, my mom and I visited a popular botanical garden in 2019. The area is about a 5 mile walk through a Japanese inspired garden and it's filled with all sorts of sub-tropical flowers. We walked around and looked at everything and had a pleasant conversation and it was a nice, sunny day. Later we went to a peach orchard and picked peaches to put into a pie later that day. At the time it felt very normal and even a bit boring, but I would have loved to do something like that this year.

This is the most memorable music festival I've ever been to. All my friends are around me as we walk to the main stage to listen to our favorite artist for the third time. The lights set up by production mixed in with the night sky are the perfect visuals to complement the music. There are large crowds of people everywhere and everyone has smiles on their faces. The Ferris Wheel to the right on the stage has a long line, but from being on it prior I know the line is worth the wait.

I talked nervously but honestly to my doctor. At times I may have seemed bored, calm and a little jittery. The doctor of mine listened and gave his opinion as well as advice. I felt secure in the room but shameful because I wasn't normal.

My boyfriend and I would meet up with friends to watch football games at parties at a friend's house.  Life was normal and exciting as the relationship was still new and I was still figuring him out.  I liked meeting his friends and we all love football.

A friend and I went up to Rexburg to visit my sister and another friend, who are roommates. We played table board games, watched some videos on Disney+, hung out, and had dinner. We enjoyed each other's company and generally just relaxed. It was a nice break for my daily routine.

I see myself and a group of friends sitting around a table at a local korean bbq restaurant waiting for meats to arrive.  As the grill is heating up, we're discussing our everyday lives about work, family, activities, etc.  The server brings the tray of meats on a large plate and places them on the grill. We watch eagerly as the steaks, ribs, brisket, pork and other cuts are cooking.  We snack on side dishes as we await and once done, we quickly dig into the meats.

I visualized what I saw when taking a test for my calculus class two semesters ago. The room was lined with grids of desks with the professor standing at the front of the class reading a book. I had my formula sheet on a desk next to mine, because my professor recognised that having a formula sheet would not provide a huge advantage to anyone during the test. At the front of the class, I see a chalk board that has the start and end time of the test written on it. On my desk is a ten page packet of calculus problems, one that was extremely difficult, and made me feel very stressed. All around me are my peers, who somehow seem to feel less stressed than me, but stressed all the same.

A family of about twelve is sitting around a table laughing while exchanging gifts in a swapping game. There is lots of smiles and everyone is anxious to get their turn rolling the dice and drawing a number from the jar.

We attended Disney World in mid-February to run in a half-marathon. The even took place at EPCOT, we ran to and through the Magic Kingdom and ended up back at EPCOT. There were more than 10,000 participants in the race and we were shoulder-to-shoulder most of the way. After the 13.1 miles we celebrated in a large field and then proceeded to enjoy a day at the theme parks.

Wade Oval Wednesday was a weekly event in my area in which food trucks, musicians, and other various activities gathered in a public space.  I specifically remember the crowd dancing to the live music (particularly a lot of children) while I was looking for a food truck line that wasn't too long with my boyfriend.  While I was doing so, I remember being excited about all the cute dogs there.  It was a sunny day, but there was a nice breeze that made it a comfortable temperature.
I woke up on Christmas Day to see a small present on my desk. I decided to open it, a behold: an Iphone!

It was my best friend's birthday and most of us were able to get together to go to a restaurant we've been dying to try (it wasn't that good, after all) and then we decided to spontaneously to go to karaoke afterwards. It was a really fun and carefree night. It started off poorly cause the birthday girl was super stressed and had some transportation issues and was late, but then it ended with lots of good alcohol, pizza, and good memories.

I'm sitting at the school library in the secluded area not many students know about. I am at a large L-shaped desk facing the large windows that show trees and a sidewalk right outside. I have my laptop out, and a couple of textbooks on the desk with me.

Two girls are at the Royal Ontario Museum on a date. They're extra happy because they're a long distance couple, so they don't get to see each other very often. The shorter one giggles a lot, pulling her girlfriend close to her and saying things in Latin. They wander around the museum, giggling and gently kissing sometimes, mostly on the cheeks and forehead. They get especially excited when they get to the Roman exhibit and start talking really fast and smiling.

It's a Tuesday night at AC pizza.  In the back of the room are 11 people, ranging in age from their early twenties to their mid fifties.  They are seated at two different tables, but clearly know each other.  It's a Geeks Who Drink trivia night, and also someone at that table's birthday.  The two teams of friends are loud and joyful as they celebrate, teasing each other between rounds about which team is better.  They order pizza, beer and garlic bread and chatter excitedly, mostly about movies and music-- everyone is really into the film Parasite right now.  During a break, the birthday girl opens gifts.  Both teams do really well in the trivia night, taking home first and second place.

The event was a birthday party for my boyfriend. I was at a restaurant with my boyfriend, his parents, his two siblings, and three of our mutual friends. We sat at a long rectangular table. My boyfriend sat to the left of me and a friend sat to my right. I could see that the restaurant was crowded. This was before social distancing was recommended. For dessert, the waitress brought out a cake with candles and the staff sang happy birthday.
Everyone is lining up and putting on their bogu or gear. They find a partner to practice with and wait for the teacher to start the lesson by hitting the drum.

The wave was nice, the water was sparkling blue..  a lot of people was in the beach. There was no social distancing, no face mask and there was no fear of infection. The couple jumped into the wave and there was music in the background.

I see a normal family, trick or treating on halloween. They are all dressed up in costumes. They chat with their neighbors while the kids run around the yard and sidewalks. No one knows what will be coming as the new year rings in.

People are walking all around campus. Campus is busy and people are running in between classes trying to get to their classes on time. Everyone is happy and not worried about anything but passing their classes and graduating in the Spring. People are also thinking about the upcoming midterms week and are starting to worry about their grades and studying for those.
It was a fundraiser for a non-profit dog rescue. There are several baskets for raffles. A lot of tables filled with people, a buffet, a band, and a celebrity in attendance.
Sitting at the bar with a friend I was next to complete strangers talking and laughing I remember  playing pool and touching pool Q's

I can see a group of people in a cabin. These people are rowdy, drunk, and having a great time. They look like a bunch of college aged young adults enjoying life and not worrying about tomorrow. They are laughing, fixing drinks, and hanging on each other. They seem like very close friends. They have a fire lit and are huddled around it, sipping their drinks and playing cards. They seem to be taking a break from the world for only a weekend, and then they will go back to working and studying.

I remember sitting in my small living room with my family and a couple of friends. When the ball dropped, everyone shot up and started to smile and cheer, and I went around the room to embrace everyone. We had hope for the New Year, the year my friends and I would graduate high school and take the next step in our lives.

My event occurred on March 7th of this year. It was my 25th birthday party. I remember most vividly being seated at my kitchen table. My close family had come to where I live to celebrate with us, my mother, step-father, sister, and three brothers were attending. I was also in the company of three of my closest friends. At this time my friend Becky brought my birthday cake to where I was seated so they could sing "Happy Birthday." My friends lit the candles and began to sing to me. I made a wish and blew out my candles. After this I had realized my friends misspelled "Happy Birthday" with the candles they had bought. We all laughed, ate cake and spent the rest of the evening in each other's company.
I remember, the day my mom called me Philip everything is gonna be alright, I was suffering from depression

I am sitting in my lawn chair facing the outdoor stage on the courthouse square. There are people all around me but I have a good view of the stage. Musicians are playing and singing bluegrass music. The sun is shining with just a few fluffy clouds. I also see people off in a corner of the grounds dancing to the music. I am holding my phone camera and recording the current song to send to my daughter.

In March of 2015, Ruby was afraid of loosing her mother to Ovarian cancer as her brother had died the previous year in a gang related shooting. She wondered what would become of her life and it bothered her greatly

A couple stands at the the Luke Bryant farm tour concert in the roped off VIP section in the midst of a crowd.  The music blares and the attendees can smell the smell of farm and October as they connect with the soil.  There is a deep earthiness to the experience. A woman turns around in her significant others arm and makes eye contact and smiles. The connection is instant and the man returns the smile, although he hates to acknowledge that he loves her so much in public, he can't resist the moment.  The are swept up in the Autumn night.

I was watching jojo by myself and laughing at the sheer genius of the fluid animation by David Studio. However, the story was very the true masterpiece of jojo. My friends have recommend that I watch jojo bizarre adventure and I only recently just watched it.
It was the Day i graduated from The university. I had to throw a Small party with friends. Was, really a memorable day for me.
I'm at a bar, dancing with my roommate and their boyfriend. It's dark. We've had a few drinks. There are a lot of lasers, lights, etc. We look happy; we're worry free and having fun.

I see myself in my vehicle while doing deliveries upset because of how bad traffic is. I likely was given too many deliveries for the amount of traffic which is frustrating. There are cars everywhere surrounding me in the three lanes on the highway.

I am picturing a large dining room.  All the tables are filled with people enjoying their meals.  Massive pieces of meat are held by waiters to be cut and placed on customer plates.  I see a large salad bar buffet table in the back of the room.

I was working as a food vendor at a festival, for a friend's bakery where we sold cookies, brownies, etc. Everyone was so nice and happy, I have never seen so many happy people in one place. I got to enjoy the festival later with my boyfriend, we danced to the music and sat in the grass taking in the sun. I remember all of the musicians played really well, even playing the trumpets they were perfect. We met up with some groups of friends and ate food, looked at jewelry, and listened to more artists playing music. It was a beautiful sunny day and the first time I got to go to a full blown music festival.

An annual family reunion with 30+ plus members in attendance at the park.  Delicious food, excellent music, dancing, jokes, and games afoot.  Sharing memories with our elders and learning about their lives. Seeing the youngest of our family and the new additions.

I see a woman shopping at an outdoor mall.  It is Fall and she is wearing warm clothing.  She is with her husband and they are pushing their baby in a stroller.  They have just come out of a popular bath store and look very happy.  They have a bag with them from a local restaurant suggesting they have just come from dinner.
Back in Feburary 2020 we went out to chinese for the last time. I remember sitting there eating my chinese in a full resturant, no one was afraid of a virus. It smelled really good.

She is sitting in a loud, dimly light restaurant.  She is sitting with an older woman her grandmother, they are sitting in a booth across from each other waiting for their food. Their voices are raised slightly above normal as they speak to be heard over the crowd. The food comes, the younger females receive sushi while the older one has vegetable fried rice.

A group of friends and I that aren't typically together went to a fun bar in SF. They played good music and everyone had a nice time dancing. We had some drinks and met some new people. It was a great time.

I had just survived breast cancer and was finally allowed by my oncologist to get my nails done.  I was so excited to return to my favorite nail salon and see my favorite nail tech.  It was so nice to see him as it had been almost a year since I was allowed to get my nails done.  We chatted away, and I was able to get a red gel manicure and pedicure.  I spent time relaxing in the massage chair and talking to other people as well. It felt great to have life return to normal for me as I had to stay at home all of 2019 except for doctor visits and procedures.

The 4th of July last year was the only year we bought our own fireworks and blew them up and it was so fun since we never got to do it before. We also prepared the best 4th of July feast. It was one of the best 4th of July's ever.

The breeze and sunlight brightens the enviorment, as four college boys planned to meet up at the train station since they were getting ready for the movies. The day was a special moment as they rarely see eachother due to their work and their school life. Even though the threat of COVID 19 was but a foreign virus in a foreign land, they were able to hang out and watch a movie which they have all anticipated to watch.
I am very friendly with my brothers, sisters and uncles whom I have not seen for a long time.I couldn't understand what I was going to do when I got close to everyone, I lost my language with joy.
I see people gathered at my shop. Holding drinks and having fun.

I saw them come into the restaurant so I started preparing the drink that the woman always had at lunch. They proceeded to wave hello and went to a booth along the back wall of the restaurant. They were a handsome couple who always came in cheerful and hungry. As they took off their winter coats, their favorite server, Damian greeted them and started chatting with the couple. He proceeded to take their food order while they laughed during the comversation.
My girlfriend and I are sitting across from each other at a restaurant table. There are people at the tables nearby us and waiters walking between them.

It was my granddaughter, Roslyn's 5th birthday party. We went to a big park that had a lot of play equipment and set up the presents, drinks, and snacks on a cement table that was on a cement pad. There were several children and a lot of adults there. It was a bit windy and we had to anchor the plastic table cloth we put down with various things like cans of soda so it wouldn't blow away. There were two other tables and adults were sitting at them chatting while the kids ran around on the playground. I was talking to family and playing a mobile game with my grandson Aiden.

On a nice Sunday afternoon, Megan (me) and her friends from church are eating a delicious lunch together following their weekly church worship. They are discussing relatively mundane topics like school and various TV shows, and occasionally mention the COVID 19 outbreak. They do not think it is likely that the outbreak would spread to New Jersey, where they live.

I live in a different state from most of my family. I see us all together when they came to visit me before the pandemic struck. I see us all gathered together at a restaurant, we are drinking and sharing food and having a great time without any regard to distancing ourselves or the people around us. I see a way of life that was not so long ago but seems absolutely distant right now. I see my elderly mother interacting with her family without a concern in the world. I see us all happy and relaxed.

The sun is warm. The family is all together. I am hugging everyone. It has been a long time since we have all been together and I am excited to see everyone after we have all traveled from different parts of the country (and world) to be together.
A guy moving transferring from one train to another, with a lot of people walking along with him. He is listening to music from his phone; a lot of people are doing the same.

People excitedly find they're seats in the premium recliners. People of all ages grab snacks and situate themselves for the show that is about to start. The smell of popcorn and cheap nacho's wafts through the air as people noisily slurp oversized and overpriced sodas and cocktails. Excitement buzzes throughout the room as people silence they're phones and the lights dim. Trailers roll and everyone laughs and whispers with hushed excitement for the main show.
I see mustangs everywhere. In the parking lot, revving their engines. In line to park idling loudly and leaving the show doing burnouts The Whole way down the street

I am sitting on a couch in an apartment in New York. It is dark outside. I hear car horns and other sounds of the city. My wife and daughter are across from me talking. And food is cooking on the stove.

I'm sitting in second row seats behind the players bench. I can hear them talking to each other and the sound of skates on the ice. I can see players on the ice making plays and trying to score a goal.

I entered the church and was immediately greeted by many friends and family from church. We would hug and see how each of our weeks had been. The children would be running around playing tag while we waited for church to start. We were able to sing, and learn about God, and worship together, encouraging each other for the week ahead. I felt like I belonged and was a part of something important.

I am in the ski shop at work, I have just finished calibrating a pair of skis when my manager drops off a pair of system mount skis and tells me to take care of them quickly. No masks, just the cozy, relatively small and hidden ski shop with the overhead light and tools on the wall at my disposal.

lots of people dancing and enjoying drinks. theres two levels to the building and im on the upper level. the band has a great production crew because the lights and lazers are very colorful and energizing. the building is packed on the lower level and comfy on the upper level.

People are all around me. Joyful, smiling, drinking, laughing. It is my birthday party, I share with my twin sister. We are enjoying it to the fullest. Not a care in the world. Swimming, and having cocktails.

I am working at Chilis as service manager. I am speaking with my team pre shift letting them know the goals and specials for the day. What drinks we are offering, what the margarita of the day is. Also doing a recognition for great customer comment for  a server.

Fox Day is an event at the college I work at that happens every year. The President declares it a holiday and everyone does whatever they want all day. Students usually go to the beach. Staff and faculty stay home and enjoy a day off. At the end of the day, we gather as a community to have a picnic with students and faculty. There are big tables in the middle of a lawn and we line up to eat barbecue. There is ice cream for the children and lemonade and cookies. Music is playing and we gather on picnic blankets or at tables with friends. Children of staff and faculty play on the lawn. It's a wonderful end to a fun day.

On valentines day, my husband and I went to Logan's for a steak.  It was wonderful. We had drinks, salad, and most important, steak. I didn't realize that it would be the last restaurant visit I would make until...i don't even know. I had the outlaw ribeye, med rare, loaded potatoes, and margaritas.

After a stressful work day I like to work out. I've been active for my whole life. A little more than 2 years ago I found OrangeTheory Fitness. It seemed a little bougie - the kind of place where you only find skinny white trophy wives head to toe in lululemon gear. I fell in love after my first class. the sense of community is just so intense. This particular day was the first time I had seen a few of my favorite coaches since celebrating my 2-year OTF anniversary. I stuck around after class to catch up with them. While we were laughing and having a good time, my favorite coach asked me when I was going to start coaching classes. I laughed. He asked again, but this time with a serious look on his face. He continued, offering me a coaching position. It was something that I had thought would be so cool to do, but so far out of my reach. It left me stunned. Speechless. I was happy, excited, confused, all at the same time.

Typically after working a very long day, a few of my colleagues and I will go out for drinks and food during happy hour at a local bar. They are usually loud and packed with people. I smell alcohol and I see people laughing, and enjoy themselves eating and drinking. There is typically a game on TV where all the people at the bar are huddled around.
We are at the gym in the workout room, there is a teach and 4 students. There's music playing as the teacher gives yoga and dance instruction and the 4 students follow her lead

I drove up to a friend's house with the board game we played that night. I sat with people and chatted while we waited for everyone to arrive. After everyone had arrived, we started playing only for one of the people to realize that they had locked their keys inside of their car. The group spent the next hour using a clothes hanger to unlock the car so that we could resume the game. After the keys were retrieved we finished the game and then everyone went back home.

Basically I am in a bar with me and my friend playing pool. I am watching from the perspective of the bartender and we are at the very corner shooting ball. We had a Pineapple Malibu Rum and we feel kind of tipsy, but not wasted.
The event was my wedding. The day was nice, and invloved lots of people and a very easy-going safe feeling

My sister and I are shopping at the thrift store. We go thrift store shopping together every other Thursday. I enjoy the time I spend with my sister shopping as we don't get to spend as much time together as I would like to. I look forward to shopping with my sister as it is a great time we spend together catching up on things.

I am standing in line at the buffet in my uncles house. I am talking to a cousin of mine. There are several people packed in really close. I am grabbing plate and going through the whole buffet. I pick up things I like and don't touch the really spicy food.

In October 2019, m husband and I relocated 1200 miles from our home state, our family and our friends.  We bought our retirement home and were excited to learn all about our new area.  After unpacking, ordering furniture and settling in, we started to explore our area.  We went to a couple of restaurants, noting all the new restaurants and tourist attractions and specialty stores and markets we were excited to go to.  We got busy with the holidays, and come January we wanted to start to explore our area.  We did not get to do much at all before the pandemic hit.

I sat at the pool in the early afternoon, then went out to eat. Later I got ready with my friends and hit the town. We went dancing on a party bus and went to multiple clubs. Made it back to the hotel room in the early hours of the morning, after stopping to pick up more food.

Before the virus, everybody went to church the same way...came in the front door where tables and chairs are set up. Stopped and said hi to people who are already there and drinking coffee waiting for mass to start. Then we go into church as usual, and sat at our regular pew and waited for mass to start. When mass started, we sang the entrance song, attended the mass, received communion and then at the end, we'd go back into the communal room, have coffee and donuts and socialize for about 15 minutes then leave.

A company is moving offices. A few employees including myself are unpacking crates and putting items away in the new office. They are putting bins that are numbered to each person in the office and referring to the floor plan of where people are going to be sitting. There is an air of excitement while everyone is trying to work as quickly as possible. Cubicles are being reconstructed in the new space which has been hired out to a third party from this company. The location of this new office is excellent as it overlooks the baseball stadium.

Looking in, I see a mother who has a very small baby and 2 older children. They are celebrating in their own way. A very small tree sits in the corner and a few modest gifts are opened by the small children while the baby plays with the wrapping paper. Everyone is having a good time.

Four women (sisters and cousins) were having dinner to celebrate the birthday of one of the group members. Gatherings like this were something we all enjoyed on a regular basis -- not just for birthdays, but for restaurant week in winter and summer and anytime we hadn't been together for awhile so we could all catch up with each other. We really enjoyed these dinner events, with lots of laughs, love and great food. Research was done by one of the group members to find places that we would undoubtedly enjoy with an emphasis on well known chefs. At the end of this dinner, it was suggested we do this again for the next birthday coming up, which was going to be a big number. The pandemic blew that whole idea right out of the water.

After Erica's pinning ceremony where she became a graduate of University of Rochester's nursing degree program, she gathered with her friends and family at a local restaurant to celebrate.  Her mother and father, her spouses and children and several other relatives and friends were there.  Everyone ordered their own choice from the menu as they sat around the big table reserved for the party.  Delicious food was served, drinks were served.  Happy conversations were heard all round the table.  It was a joyous warm social celebration of the accomplishments of a beloved family member and friend.

I had a meetup with some friends for dinner. We went to a Japanese sushi restaurant. We sat at a long wooden table Everyone was having a good time, carefree, sharing food, talking about what was happening in our lives. I remember we were celebrating someone's birthday. We did talk about what was happening in China with covid-19, but that was an event happening far away and not a personal concern.

It was a hot 4th of July in Columbia Maryland.  Thousands of people were gathered to watch fireworks at the Lakefront.  Everyone is crowded together.  Someone throws a large firecracker.  This makes me very uneasy.  It is nice to see everyone together though.

About a hundred friends and family gathered outside for the ceremony all sitting closely next to each other. Everyone talking and greeting each other before things begin. Having drinks. A marachi band begins to play after the ceremony finished. The reception taking place inside with food drinking and dancing.

A middle-aged woman is in the aisle of the local grocery store, looking at the selection of fresh vegetables. She's wearing a heavy, black coat, long pants, white tennis shoes, and a black winter scarf. She is not wearing a hat and her face is uncovered. She is holding a green pepper in her left hand, and a plastic bag in her right hand.

Every year since my child started school ( I am raising a grandson) he just went into grade 7 this year, 2020 so 2019 was his last year i would be able to go to his Christmas assembly. I am a person with a huge fear of people so walking into a crowded room to watch him was a big challenge for me. I even missed the previous year because i couldn't get myself to walk in alone. I can vividly remember going to Walmart without wearing a mask and social distancing. There was nothing to think about; shopping was a breeze compared to the way it is now. I am inside the hookah lounge where I periodically meet up with my friend. We are now sitting in the back room which is a large and almost empty area. Three people walking on the beach. It is slightly windy, they are huddled in jackets and the wind occasionally whips their hair. Everyone is dressed for the cooler day, with jackets, some having shorts instead of pants. Joggers run along the boardwalk, unaffected by the wind gusts.

I wake up and it is warm inside and out. The sun is glaring through the windows and I feel great. Nothing really happens, other than me being able to appreciate that we are all still here. They are attending a concert. There are many people here. It is a large crowd. In the front a lady and a man sit down. They are  talking. I step into the office where I work with six other colleagues, our IT office. I see myself and all the other guys sitting at our cubicles getting started for the day. I foolow myself to the elevator, then to the employees cubicle, and see me get to work.

i am bent over my frame and using my needle punch to complete the net. there is sergio and aviva there talking and helping customers. people walk by down hayes street. sometimes they stop and when i turn my head towards them they smile and wave and then walk on. i am in the window of the shop and working on my piece. people occasionally stop in and ask me what i am doing or compliment the work. when there is no one in the shop i listen to sergio and aviva talk and sometimes they chat with me but mostly each other. they try on clothes that are in the store. i take breaks and rest my hands or use the restroom. i take breaks and walk next door or down the street.

the concert is with the concert bamd. the players walk onstage, and the audience quiets. the director walks up to the microphone and gives the opening spiel. he is short and a little old, and talks humorously. then, as he walks back, the lights dim. the band starts playing with the conductor's wave of a baton and they are playing a classical piece. the piece is energetic and they play it pretty well, but it it clear that it is a challenging piece. they are very focused and concentrated on playing to the best of their ability, and the music sounds good.

I am a visual story teller, and was set up in my craft booth for a local Christmas Craft Festival, My booth was filled with my crafts, and I had a Christmas tree set up with ornaments, and special giveaways for purchases. People were coming in looking at my crafts and asking questions, and purchasing items. A true friendly holiday spirit. My husband was there helping me, and we were having a wonderful time, as we chatted with customers and had many happy people, that were thrilled with their free gift for their purchases. There was Christmas music, and the wonderful smell of hot spiced cider. It was a great day. We made decent money, and had a great time, so in a way it wasnt like "work",

Before the pandemic, I used to visit regularly a certain friend with a chronic illness.  The last time I saw him, I made the long drive and arrived at his place.  I saw him sitting at the window waiting for my arrival and motioned to him that he could stay put, since he has trouble walking, and that I would let myself in since the door was ajar.  We were generally limited in where we could go already given his circumstances, so we moved to his room, and I watched from his bed as he played computer games.  At some point, I nodded off and upon waking, he told me that he would have woke me, but that he was sure I was tired.  It made me feel sad that I had come such a distance to see him, and more or less the first thing I did was fall asleep.  Still, once I had roused myself again, I made some coffee and we went for a slow walk around the house together, laughing and making jokes, generally with some shade of dark humor.  I remember the weather was sunny and unseasonably warm that day, and there was a light breeze that made everything seem happier and sadder at the same time to me.  I had only spent about two hours there, but given his illness, and that he seemed tired, I thought it best to adjourn for the day, promising that I would come back in a few weeks to see him again.

I'm a doctor on a cruise ship. We are out in the ocean and I am called to the medical center. As I enter the room, I see a man setting in a chair by the bed. The bed has a lady on it and she looks like she is in pain. The nurse has already started and I V and has given her some anti-nausea medication, but the lady has thrown that up. I ask her what is going on and were the pain is. She tells me about the pain and have this is the third time this has happened. I give her pain meds and keep her till the pain is gone.

As I sit in my seat for my chemistry lecture, I see fellow students settling into their seats around me. Just moments before, I was crammed into an overcrowded bus with other students. We were almost packed like sardines. From the windows of the bus, I could see the usual rush of students after class was done. Dozens of students poured out from the lecture halls to fill the road with bikes. The bus came to a halt, lurching me forward from where I was grabbing a pole. Hurriedly, I walked to my lecture hall and took a seat. Gradually, more students started to fill the lecture hall. Although, probably half the class didn't show up.
He is in the park along with many people. There are no restrictions of any kinds. Anyone can go where they like. Theaters and restaurants are full. Everything is nice.

It was at a BTS concert at MetLife with about 40+ thousand people present. Everyone was singing, dancing, laughing and screaming along with the music, shaking their lightsticks while the group performed. I can see myself in the stands, it's hard for me to stand up for too long, but even when I had to sit down I was still singing and using the lightstick. The lightshow lit up the night. There were fireworks and the sensation of an enormous festival was overwhelmingly beautiful. It was especially amazing when there were songs that we all sang along to in unison. There is nothing like hearing that many people sing together with their favorite artists.

The club was very crowded, and people were packed in front of stage and talking  with each other.  The stage was empty, but the band's equipment was set up, so it would only be a few minutes before they started playing.  The house lights went down and everyone cheered.  The band took to the stage and without a word, began playing the opening song from their latest album.  It was very loud, and everyone at the concert was excited and danging around the stage.

The event I'm thinking of is the last time I walked my son to school, just before the quarantine. It was cold, but not bitterly so. We only live a few blocks from the school, so it was a relatively short walk. We left the house, strolled to the end of the block, and made a right turn. I remember that my son and I were discussing one of his favorite video games. He described the facets of the game that he enjoys most, and I compared it to some of the games I played back in the day. There's one busy intersection we need to cross, and I remember the crossing guard on duty that day. Once past the intersection, we walked one more block to the school. Upon our arrival we said our goodbyes, and I returned home.

My sister and I go out to eat quite often, or at least we did til the supposed pandemic hit. I am thinking of a time at one of our favorite restaurants in a nearby town. It's a Mexican restaurant that we go to a lot. It's a nice quiet place with fabulous food. We always sit in a booth facing each other. We always order some wine with our food. There are not a lot other customers while we are there so it's pretty fast service. We look out the big windows and enjoy our conversation.

I am sitting in a desk in my applied calculus class at community college. It's 10:15 AM. I am wearing a hoodie and sweatpants. I brought a gray backpack. I am sitting in the right most row of desks in the second to last desk from the back. I have my phone on my desk, as well as my notebook. I also have my mechanical pencil and calculator out. Although I try to pay attention, I also get distracted on my phone browsing discord or reddit or whatever else. I talk to my friend Reina. At the time she is my best friend, but soon we will have become boyfriend and girlfriend. She is truly amazing and I love her so much.

I see a large group of people, mostly women, sitting around a table. There are so many people and more continue join them, and each time a new person comes to the table, the ones who are there shift their chairs to make room for the newcomer. Everyone is drinking tea or coffee, talking, laughing. One person is passing around their phone to show off picture of their grandchildren. The only man at the table periodically gets up from his seat to refill someone's coffee cup. Some people are talking across the table to each other, while others are talking in groups of 2 or 3. They are enjoying being together. The sound of their voices and laughter rings across the room.

I was going to a variety of bars close to the city center with my best friend at the time for my 21st birthday. We got there in an uber after spending time at his house with his brother and brother's friends. I was very buzzed and did not have to worry about bumping into other people or possibly being coughed on. It was okay for us to wait in long lines next to strangers and drink things indoors in crowded bars. We talked to strangers without masks on and just had a really nice night. At the end of the night we were able to get in a rideshare and go back to his house without any worry. It was really nice.

A girl sits in a Greyhound bus with her knees pulled in against her chest. She's looking out the window with her earbuds in, listening to music on her phone. The scenery she's passing is all familiar - the journey is four hours long. Right now, she - and all the passengers on the bus - are passing through Johnstown, Pennsylvania. This is about when she always starts to feel carsick. The smell of the bus makes her queasy. It's kind of sweet and very artificial and totally unpleasant - like when you spray febreeze over a blanket to cover up a smell rather than throwing it into the washing machine.

In October os 2019 my roommate Tiffany and I threw a Halloween party for our family and friends. We had many guests there, probably totaling about 40. The party was a great deal of fun. There was a variety of elaborate, humorous costumes. One gay couple I'm friend with came dressed as "Adam and Steve" (a parody on Adam and Eve). My roommate, my cousin, my friend and I had dressed up as the Powerpuff Girls that year. Another friend of mine came dressed as a police officer. My cousin Tara was the center of attention at one point, dancing wildly to a song she enjoyed. I remember a few people taking videos of her dancing. We all thought it was hilarious.

There I am at a big round table at church. I'm sitting with my Bible and notes and the other girls are sitting around the table.  Our leader is teaching and we are listening.  We feel calm.  We feel connected to each other and it's an environment where we feel safe.  We are now discussing the questions.  The girls get sidetracked and we all laugh.  They are so fun to be with.  I like hearing their questions and I see myself laughing.  We take prayer requests and the girls pray for each other.  As the group finishes they thank me for leading.

It was a beautiful mostly sunny early July end of the day in downtown Charleston West Virginia.We are at Power Ballpark to watch a class A minor league baseball game between the West Virginia Power, an affiliate of the Major League's Pittsburgh Pirates, and the Blue Claws, an affiliate of the Philadelphia  Phillies. The stadium was mostly full, although not completely, considering it was July 4th weekend, and the fireworks display usually put on by the team for the holiday is usually very striking. The game was pretty routine through the first several innings, but in the bottom of the 3rd, the Power lineup was able to string together 3 hits around an error by the shortstop to take a 3 to nothing lead.

The event that I pictured was taking a yoga class at a barcade on Sunday morning with some friends. I'm near the bar and the instructor is in front of me, with one friend next to me and two friends behind me. On the other side of me is arcade games. I see all the paint on the walls and the drinks listed on the board behind the bar. After yoga, we went to brunch at a nearby restaurant. The restaurant specializes in French pastries and baked goods. The restaurant is very modern and beautifully decorated. I'm sitting across from my friend and our two friends are next to us. I order a salmon baguette, which was delicious, and felt so nice and healthy after completing a challenging yoga class. The water that they serve is infused with lemon and herbs, which was also super refreshing. Even though it was still February, and rather cold, the sun was shining and kept me warm.

The event is buying my dad a new car. I recall taking him to test drive cars in early February at our local dealerships. We test drove at nearly every dealership. In mid February I began contacting some dealerships outside of my local area to get a good deal on a car. Within 48 hours, I was able to come to a deal with a dealer 2 hours away. I remember being excited for getting the price under what I wanted to pay, then going to my bank to get the cashiers check, the following day we drove out to the dealer, I signed the papers, and within an hour we were on our way. I was very happy with the way things turned out and was quite optimistic for this year.

I see myself get to a meeting spot where I am supposed to meet with my friends.  Everyone gets to the meeting spot and we take one car to go out shopping for the day.  All the people in the car are talking and laughing and look happy, including myself.  The group goes to different stores and browses, sometimes buying things. The group goes to lunch, still all talking and laughing, happy to have left kids and husbands at home. at the end of the day the car goes back to the meeting spot. Everyone gets out and chats for a little while longer. I see myself get back in my car and start to drive home.

I got to go for a walk in one of the first snows of the winter season that happened near the winter holidays.  It was during the day but because it was snowing, the sun wasn't shining.  It wasn't snowing super hard like a blizzard, but just a steady kind of wet snow that quickly began to cover everything.  It was so beautiful and made the earth quiet and peaceful in a way that only snow can.  It accumulated quickly.  I could feel the flakes on my face.  The air was cold and bracing but I was bundled up quite well.  It was just such a lovely feeling to be out with the trees and walking in the neighborhood and hearing the wind in the branches while everything covered up with the new snow.  It made everything clean and white and like there was marshallow dropped on everything.  It was so peaceful.  I could hear my own thoughts for the first time in a long time as had been under some stress.  And the fact that it was near the holidays was like a gift from the universe.  This is my favorite winter activity and I can only imagine what snow must be like for the first time for someone who has never experienced it before.  It was so relaxing and yet invigorating at the same time.  I felt quite refreshed by the time I finished my walk.  I don't know if I am supposed to keep writing.  The next button in available but more space keeps showing up.  And it says to keep writing until it fills the space below.  But the space doesn't ever seem to fill up and end.  Please make it clearer so we don't end up sitting here writing unnecessarily for an hour.  I am going to move on.  Hope that's ok.

I walked into the movie theaters for what I didn't know would be the last time in a while. I remember purchasing tickets for my son daughter husband and myself. we proceeded to the concession stands one by one. We all picked out our favorite snacks. Me and my husband chose chololates and my son and daughter chose more sour sweets and things like that. We also got nachos and slurps. The movie theatre was pretty full but we were still able to find seating together. We enjoyed the movie as a family and I remember it was funny we thoroughly enjoyed it. we did not know that wou8ld be the last time.

I am going up the stair stepper slowly and holding on to the rails. I am trying to hold onto the rails less because I know that I do less work when I'm taking some of the weight in my arms. I am annoyed at the guy across the gym for screaming while he drops his weights aggressively. I am trying to watch hulu on my phone but it's hard because the stair stepper doesn't have a good place to put phones which is really annoying so I have to put it in the cup holder. Luckily this makes me have to stay at the top of the stair stepper because if not I can't see my shows. I can't watch shows without captions because I am easily distracted. I should watch podcasts.

I gave my senior design mid-term demonstration in person about a week before the coronavirus rendered everyone indoors. I did not think at the time that it would be my last in-person presentation for a while. The presentation was kind of boring, especially because three other groups had to present. What I remember most about that day is probably what happened after the presentations. After the presentations, we went to the bar with a couple other groups in the middle of the afternoon and celebrated with alcohol until we were too drunk to hang around anymore. The bar was crowded even in the afternoon.

My brother and I are at a thrift store in Auburn, Alabama. It's called the Restore and is located on Opelika Road. We are standing in front of shelves full of music CD's and going through them looking for things we can sell. We find a couple of rare CD's on the Wounded Bird label. We keep going through the CD's and find a small heavy metal collection. There are Iron Maiden and Judas Priest CD's that look rare. We cull together about 60 CD's and take them in a cart up to the counter to purchase them. We are told they are 50 cents each and they bag the CD's for us, then I insert my credit card and get my receipt for these items. My brother and I grab the bags and walk out of the building. We put the CD's in the back behind my seat.

I'm at church sitting with my friends Jessie, Lise, and Mel.  We're holding a "souper bowl" fundraiser.  Each family makes a pot of soup and everyone in the congregation tries multiple soups.  Then each person contributes money to the soup that they like best.  I tried 4 different soups that day and contributed about $20.  There were roughly 70 people attending the event.   My soup came in 4th place but my friend Jessie's came in 3rd.  After some general chatting, we began planning for vacation bible school that was scheduled to take place in June 2020.  I was taking notes and helping to pick dates and activities.

IT A JUMP PARK AND CHILDREN ARE ALL PLAYING LAUGHING AND RUNNING AROUND. PARENTS ARE EITHER SITTING NEAR BY TALKING  TO ONE  ANOTHER OR PLAYING WITH THEIR CHILDREN. NO ONE IS WEARING A MASK OR STAYING FAR FROM ONE ANOTHER. THE KIDS ARE ALL INTERACTING WITH ONE ANOTHER. IT IS A FUN PLACE TO BE

I took a work trip with a few coworkers to Taiwan. It was about the second or third time I had taken business trips there, so I was excited to go with a colleague. I recall that even though I do not particularly enjoy travel (i.e. dealing with airports, security, etc), it was nice to be able to travel freely and enjoy business class. I was excited to be able to also see relatives in Taiwan and enjoy good food everywhere. I also appreciated that I was able to stay in a fancy hotel in the downtown area, which provided close proximity to lots of good food and shopping. It was very convenient to get around and overall the trip was really enjoyable.

a woman playing at an arcade game (the penny pusher). Another woman is with her, they are a couple. They're spending money on the arcade without worrying about the consequences. The first woman is playing while the other watches. It is the first woman's birthday and she really enjoys the penny pusher games. They win tokens that can be redeemed in the arcade for prizes. They spend a while browsing the prizes and deciding what to do with the tokens to commemorate this time spent in the arcade together. Ultimately they leave together, happy and feeling at peace with each other. The money was well spent.

I see groups of people gathering, anticipating heartfelt hugs from each other.  Everyone is smiling and eager to share stories of their latest adventures. I see myself smiling and laughing, folks are excited to get my patented good hugs and greet them with 'Welcome Home' to our annual family gathering.  Many folks are offering food or beverages and finding out where people are camping over the weekend, inviting each other to campsites for songs or feasts.  Kids are reuniting and excitedly sharing stories and antsy to play on the playground.  Dogs are sniffing each other, seemingly as excited as their owners to see each other again.

I see myself at the get-together with others. It is held at a couple's house. There are several people there. We are sitting around the backyard. There is hugging when someone new arrives. Food is shared on a platter. People pick from it as they please. There is also a new drink someone brought. Several people take a drink out of the same glass, as well as myself.

I was at the local college, taking a community course demonstrating Fixed mindset vs Growth mindset.  I was in the college's library in a room reserved for this class. I was with my mother, and about 8 other ladies, not including the instructors. The room was quiet, clean, and had good lighting from windows and fixtures in the room.  I sat at a table, accompanying my mother.  The class was in 4 parts, each part took place on a Saturday morning.  I really enjoyed learning the material they taught and use things from that course in my everyday dealings with my family and community around me now.

I attended a showing of Avengers Endgame on the opening night. The theater was full of people: every seat was filled and people were sitting next to each other. I was seated in the middle of the theater, with people on either side of me. People were eating and drinking during the movie, and the crowd enthusiastically reacted to major events as they unfolded on the screen in front of me. I saw people decked out in all their Avengers gear, gathering in knots to to talk before the movie began, discussing where to find seats for their group in the crowded theater. Afterwards, people walked out of the theater together, and strangers talked  about the movie they had just seen.

I'm attending a concert at the basketball gym at my university.  The headlining band is currently famous nationwide, but I came to see the opening act, as the lead singer is a famous actor turned singer.   I have a really good seat near the stage, the music is pumping, and the crowd is dancing in time to the beat as the singer belts out a tune.

Getting out of the car i could not wait to go inside Michaels and rummage through the yarn, Winter always had new colors of yarn. Heading to that sections got me excited as they always have sales. Rummaging through the piles of yarn, matching colors I immediately picked out 8 skeins, Touching the yarn always gives me comfort, reduces my anxiety, was getting into my mind on how many hats and scarves I could make to donate. I felt like I need some cotton yard also to make some scrbbers for the dishes as they are fun to make also. I easily ended up spending 50 bucks. I checked the clearance bin also as I could sometimes find really good deals in there. I had to check the wreath section and ribbon section to as I was working on a spring wreath and indecisive about the colors I wanted to actually use. Checking the planner section I also got a few new sticker backs for my daily planner as I had a lot to keep up with at times with all my appointments, work and such. Beads are a favorite too and I had to see what was on sale in that section too. I got my purchases together and finally went to the car. Grateful I didnt end up spending a fortune.

I am at a Sunday league ultimate frisbee game. We play on afternoons every Sunday in the fall and spring seasons, and I've been playing with this team for five years. We start the game with a team huddle, where we stand in a circle, maybe with arms around each other, and talk about the game that is about to happen.  We are all friends and sometimes don't see each other at anything else, so it is a nice social event as well as a good for exercise. There are also good mental health benefits from it, both from its social benefits and its health benefits. Because it is Oregon the ground is often soft and sometimes even muddy from recent rain. It often rains as we play.

The store hours of that day were operating like usual which was 24 hours and something of a major convenience to me and my lifestyle. I do avoid shopping at regular high traffic hours for numerous reasons. So having that available to me has helped tremendously . I walk in as normal and usual and grab a basket without any sort of preventative measures. There are still other shoppers at these less than traffic times, but it's bearable and everyone just goes about their shopping. Once I was finished with my shopping I then proceeded to the self checkout aisles and bagged and paid for my groceries.

I was talking to Henry about the Coronavirus while working at a gym. We were talking about the recent outbreak in the nursing home in Seattle, Washington. Henry told me that this was just the beginning, and that we would be missing this present moment weeks and months from now as the virus spread. I looked to the gym and looked at the people present to capture the moment, in case Henry was right. I remember thinking, it could not possibly become so bad and perhaps the spread may stay on the west coast of the United States. Henry was a wise person and had some insight to the pandemic at hand I've realized.

I am sitting on the ground it the kid that I care for. He is passing balls to me through the tunnel. He throws them way too fast and hits me in the stomach. I verbalize ouch and then throw it back to him. He laughs and continues throwing the ball to me. We keep throwing balls at each other until he runs out of balls in his bag. Afterwards, I say it's time to clean up and he does so. First he puts all the balls away in his bag and afterwards the tunnel. The tunnel gets put above the couch and I say thank you.

The family of 5 took a 3 hour drive to Chicago. They stayed at a nice hotel, and seemed happy. The kids were excited to walk around the city, and the family enjoyed a good dinner at a unique, spy themed restaurant. The next day the family went shopping, and went to see "Blippi Live". The kids enjoyed the musical, and the parents had fun watching the excitement on their kid's faces. The family went back to the hotel and swam, excited to take their one year old daughter into a pool for the first time. They left the next morning, tired from all the walking but happy for a fun, family trip together.

I pull up to the Taekwondo gym and enter. As I remove my shoes and place those & my personal items in a cubby, I look around at who has come to tonight's class. I stretch and talk to friends in the class, asking about their day/sport related qns/chit chat. We wait until the previous class is let out and immediately enter the mat. A junior instructor warms us up and we soon begin our class. There is laughter and some frustration for us perfectionists if we don't get a kick just right. We all clap over other's accomplishments. After cooling down, we bow out and amid chatting, gather our things to leave.

I go into GameStop and hang out watching the employee's interact with each other and the customers. sometimes I bring in a tablet or even a keyboard. I generally hang out from 10am (opening hours) to about 2pm when I head home. While there sometimes I'll buy little stuff but not always. It depends on if I find anything of interest. When no one is around sometimes I'll talk to the employee's or if there are customer's I play on my phone or tablet. I often bring an energy drink and food.

I'm at six flag for their Halloween event, my boyfriend's family business gets private tickets every year. I'm wandering around the park looking for the next haunted house. There's people around me, sometimes it is crowded but most times it's thinner than the average day at the park. We find this virtual reality tried instead and decide to go on it, I'm sitting right next to my boyfriend we a few other people and we shoot aliens and stuff in 3d, it feels like I can reach out and touch the things on the screen. We got special glasses to see everything and had to turn them back in after the ride for the next group to use.

Jen had a winter solstice party at her house. As John parked the car he accidentally backed it into a pole, for which he was very apologetic. Jen's house was warm and smelled nice. Her mother was there and was a friendly and warm person. The house was small and cozy and really uniquely and well-decorated. There were very few people were there but then the living room filled up. There were snacks, drinks, and people chatting with each other about where they live, where they work. Jen's mom expressed an interest in going birding with John and his wife. Jen had two cats. One was friendly and let visitors pet him.

My son and I went into Twin Dragons to place an order for take-out food, as we had regularly done once a month for several months. The restaurant is dimly lit, even in the middle of the day, and moderately busy with the last of its lunch time crowd. The owner greeted us cordially and asked what they could get for us. I placed my order, the same order I placed every month, and the owner wrote it down and rang it up. As we turned to leave, she said something teasing to me about my son--I don't remember exactly what, but maybe that we wouldn't let him have any of the food if he didn't behave. Her remark spoke to a friendly familiarity and a tacit understanding that we women were really in charge. We were all laughing as my son and I left the restaurant.

We left our apartment and walked a couple blocks to one of our favorite local spots.  It was a fairly warm day for early March, and we had had a stressful and uncertain week but we were determined to enjoy ourselves the way we normally would on a Friday night by going to our favorite neighborhood bar.  They were playing good music and we ordered a couple of draft beers and found a table.  The bar was moderately crowded even though it was still early in the evening.  When we got hungry, we ordered hot sandwiches from the deli counter inside the bar.  The sandwiches which were delicious, as always, and I recall being somewhat aware that it could be our last normal night out for a long time.
I was enjoying my vacation is I was driving through Rocky Montains in both Colorado and New Mexico and loving the scenery and sky.

This person is out with family and is visiting restaurants and walking around outside. They are chatting with others and look happy as they are walking around the area. They are taking pictures with their phone and engaging with others outside their group as well. Eventually they stop inside for a drink and sit down. They tell stories with the others in their group and everyone smiles and laughs. They order food which everyone seems to enjoy. After the meal they head outside and go to the beach. They set up some spots on the sand before heading into the water. A few of them are playing games and splashing around in the ocean.

Walking in the screen door of the shop there is always a fan running, pushing the amazing smells out into the boardwalk. as soon as i walk in there is a popcorn machine to the right, a cooler with different types of sodas to the left, and a jellybean dispenser area with all different flavors, with a hard candy dispensor after that. on the right next to the popcorn machine is where they keep the different types of fudge, with the more old fashioned candies after that, a paying station, more candies, and then you go down a slight ramp. all the different homemade ice creams are on the right, with a small room on the left where you can walk in and find giant gummy bears, lollypops, salt water taffy, and other child inspired candies like pop rocks, shark grabbers, and other fun things.

I am at Sylvan Beach with my children for a cookout and a day at the beach.  It is a sunny, hot day with a breeze coming in off the lake. We sit at a picnic table, and I start cooking hot dogs and hamburgers. My girls are unloading our food from the car. The smoke from the grill gets in my eyes, and I sweat from the heat of the grill.  I finish cooking the meat, and we sit down and eat our lunch. We then go down to the beach, which is busy but still enough room to put down our beach blanket without feeling too crowded.  The seagulls are cawing, and we lay on the blanket, and I start reading a book.  The girls go out for a swim and ask me to come, but I am into the book and stay behind.  After a few hours at the beach and exhausted from being out in the hot sun, we pack up our things and head home.

I was in the hospital for being suicidal. I went to the phych emergency room and I was so anxious. There were other teens there as well and some were out of control. tthey took our belongings can we had to wait to talk to a psych.

I see two people in the laundromat looking at their phones while they wait for their laundry to finish. They were talking about going next door to get a cup of coffee since it had been a while since they had purchased one.The laundromat is air-conditioned and cool, so that is why they are most likely inside instead of outside. There are not many people in the laundromat at this time. It is just them and the people working there.  They are mostly reading on their phones, but they will occasionally look up and talk to each other about something. At one point, they hold hands.

I flew to New York for my best friend Max's wedding. I booked a weird but interesting "micro" suite hotel to stay in near Midtown. There were lots of people visiting there from Europe and some sort of fancy event in the hotel. The actual wedding was in lower Manhattan so I suited up and took the subway. It was very crowded and full of all sorts of people, as it always is. The wedding was conducted in the traditional Jewish way in the venue hall of a beer brewery so it had a very cool "industrial chic" look to it. Lots of old friends I hadn't seen in a few years were there with me and it was great fun to catch up. We all had a 4 course meal and danced for a few hours. Once things were winding down the whole party went to a pub next door to drink and keep socializing until the early hours of the morning.  Literally zero aspects of this entire experience could have happened now, from the flight to the hotel to the crowded subway to the huge gathering to the pub. None of it.

There's a big maker faire in a library in a relatively big city in this state. There are tables from different organizations showing products, and there are people outside dancing. It's a festive atmosphere. Upstairs, there's a table with three librarians showing their work. It's really interesting: there's a "cat walk" that makes sounds when you step on different parts of cloth, and most interesting is a musical scarf. It plays sounds when you touch the jingling bells that have been sewn onto it. You can actually play a song on the scarf if you want to. People come to play the scarf. They love it!

This event is my fiance's little sister's high school graduation. We arrived at her high school and sat in tall bleachers around the football field while waiting on the ceremony to start. Everyone was dressed up and having a great time together- much of their family had traveled from all over the country to celebrate with her. It was a humid, warm evening that ended up being very pleasant- and the sun set over the farm fields during the ceremony. We could see it because it was a hilly area and our vantage point was relatively high compared to the surrounding farmland.

I am preparing myself to travel to Ohio to pick up my youngest daughter.  I am packing up my car with the few things I will need for a weekend stay, leaving most of my trunk space empty so that my daughter can put all of the things she will need for a week-long visit in Georgia.  I am filling my car's tank with gas at a truck stop, taking a break at a rest area to stretch my legs.  I arrive at my daughter's home and enjoy her company.
Everything is peaceful and calm. I am coming home and everything is just so normal. No virus, no crazy stuff on the news, It 's just a nice level of normalcy. Eating at a normal restaurant.

Driving home from the store I see a girl rocking out in her car, singing along to music I can't hear but having a really good time. She doesn't care if anyone is looking, she's in her own little world.

I think about the many mornings spent eating a continental breakfast at a Best Western in Orlando. This was a common way to spend every morning on our yearly vacation. The place was always crowded and the tables were really close together. There was never much space between us and other people at their tables. I would usually be with my father or my father and my daughter. I always loved making waffles with their waffle maker. I think about how weird it seems now being in such a small space with so many other people. I think about how great the breakfast was because of the time spent with people who are important to me before going to a theme park for a day of fun. My daughter has her own life now so the chances of her being a part of the trip in the future is very slim. I miss the times spent together at the breakfast.

There is a woman sitting at a small table by herself. She orders a jerk platter filled with Jamaican cuisine. Throughout the dinner, she watches Netflix shows and engages with the waitress serving her. Upon completing her meal, she asks for the check. She promptly pays and gives a tip, before grabbing her belongings and leaving the small restaurant.

In this scenario, there are two individuals working at a coffee shop. These two individuals include a college student (a girl) and a mid-twenties professional (male). Both individuals have worked together before, and thus have a good rapport. Both individuals are wearing company-mandated uniforms. I am sitting at a table near the entrance. I am wearing casual clothing (jeans, t-shirt). I alternate between working on personal items, and talking with the individuals working at the coffee shop. everything looks red and brown, the walls are wooden and it's raining outside really hard.  we are beside a large river.  our closest family and friends are here celebrating with us.  waiters and waitresses are running all over the place trying to keep track of everyone's orders and drinks.  my son is red in the face, having a hard time dealing with all of the noise, bustle and people.  my husband is doing a really good job mingling with everyone.  my best friends are doing what they can to help me and keep me comfortable as i try to wrangle my screaming, sweaty child.  i order yet another sweet tea to try and keep calm since i'm being pulled this way and that.

It was early December 2019 when the store found out that not only it but all stores would be closing. My family and I went on vacation to go skiing in Colorado. I'm specifically remembering the process of flying: arriving at the airport, unloading bags from the car and taking them over to the check-in desk outside, figuring out whose bag is whose and which passports will be associated with which bag, etc. My dad parked the car, so we took his bags to check them in as well, and then he met us in the line for security. I love travel and flying, so this memory is very fond. I love walking through the airport and seeing all the people, and this trip was no different. All kinds of people from all different places milling about, finding food, talking on phones, shopping at kiosks, etc. My family and I wandered through the terminal, my sister and I got coffees, we found our gate at our pace, and then folks went to go find the bathroom or settle into reading or scrolling our phones. My sister and I were sat next to each other on the plane, so we watched a movie together. I think it was Knives Out, but I can't remember totally. I always get coffee and cookies when the flight attendants bring the snack cart around. Taking off is exhilarating - I love the moment when the plane lifts off the ground and that incredible, insurmountable force of gravity is temporarily pushed back. The community of fellow travelers and the etiquette that is (or at times isn't) followed by our comrades in flight creates a sense of unity.
